<b>You can even select countries according to their ranking </b>on one or more variables. For example, you can select for study those countries having more than 3% population growth in 1993 and less than 30% female literacy.<p><b>World Guide </b>contains <b>time-sequence data for over 150 variables </b>divided into 14 statistical groups such as sex and age, health, agriculture, standard of living and environment. And if you don't like looking at numbers or lists of countries ranked according to life expectancy, don't despair. Just click on the <b><i>bar graph </i></b>or the <b><i>line graph </i></b>icon and you will be given a clear and colourful graphical comparison of life expectancy trends in Burkina Faso and the US, for example. <b><i>Population pyramids </i></b>are easily available too.<p><img align=right hspace=10 vspace=10 border=1 src="ni_pix/world_book.gif"><h3>World Guide 1995 CD-ROM includes:</h3><li><b>Unique details </b>on the new Central Asian, Eastern and Central European countries<li><b>Profile of each country </b>and its people from political, ethnic and religious viewpoints<li><b>History: </b>the evolution of the nation.<li><b>Theme texts </b>which explore population, monocultures versus diversity, the debt trap, urbanization and so on. Use the <b>full text search capabilities </b>to find and print the articles and facts you are interested in, for a particular country or for the whole world.<li><b>Amnesty International Reports 1992 to 1994. </b><p>System requirements:<br><b>Windows: </b>IBM-compatible 386 PC or higher, 4MB RAM, 3 MB hard-drive space, CD-ROM drive, Microsoft Windows 3.1, MS-DOS 4.01 or later, mouse, VGA graphics.<br><b>Macintosh: </b>Any colour or grayscale Macintosh with 4MB RAM running System 7 or later, 2MB hard-drive space, CD-ROM drive. <p><hr width=71%><p><b>TO ORDER Please send your name and address with payment to the appropriate address below. If you are not happy with the World Guide on C