<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>New Internationalist :  Issue 275</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><H3><IMG SRC="../ni_pix/nilogo.gif" WIDTH="100" HEIGHT="88" BORDER="1" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN=bottom>New Internationalist Issue 275</H3><BR><I>The material that follows has been provided by <A HREF="../NIinfo.html">NewInternationalist</A></I> <BR><HR><BR><BR><h1>BOYCOTT NESTLE!</h1><font size=+1>The campaign led by the International Nestl&eacute; Boycott Committee primarily targets Nescaf&eacute;, the corporation's flagship product. But the NI is encouraging you to boycott all Nestl&eacute; products until the company stops promoting its babymilk.  Here are the main contact points for the infant feeding campaign - together with a country-by-countryguide to Nestl&eacute; in all its various brand-name disguises.</font><p><h3>IINTERNATIONAL</h3><b>International Babyfood Action Network (IBFAN).</b><BR><b>Europe: </b>c/o GIFA, BP 157, 1211 Gen&egrave;ve 19, Switzerland. Tel: (4122)798 9164. Fax: (4122) 798 4443. Also as under Britain.<BR><b>North America:</b> see under Canada/US.<BR><b>Latin America: </b>Amaranta N90, Stantacha, Erb Prado del Est&eacute;, Caracas1080, Venezuela. Tel/Fax: (582) 977 0476.<BR><b>Asia &amp; Pacific:</b> PO Box 19, 10700 Penang, Malaysia. Tel: (604) 656 9799.Fax: (604) 657 2655.<BR><b>Africa:</b> PO Box 781, Mbabane, Swaziland. Tel: (268) 45006. Fax: (268) 44246.<p><img width=57 height=163 align=right hspace=5 vspace=5 src="boycott_perrier.jpg"><br><b>AOTEAROA/NEW ZEALAND</b><BR>There has been no action group on this issue for the past five years. Anyoneinterested in reactivating a group should contact Tul Bevan, NZ LactationConsultants Association, PO Box 29279, Christchurch. Tel: (03) 473 8677.<BR><b>Beverages:</b> Nescaf&eacute;, including Cappuccino, Classic, Expresso and FineBlend; International Roast; Andronicus; Caro; Carnation; Milo; Nesquik;Vittel and Perrier mineral waters; Nestea.<BR><b>Confectionery: </b> Kit Kat; Smarties; Rolo; Quality Street; Life Savers; MilkyBar; Milo Bar; Scorched Almonds; After Eight; Allen's confectionery, includingOddfellows, Mackintosh's Toffees, Kool mints, Raspberry Twists, Soothersand Vita C; Allen's/Heards confectionery including Barley Sugars; BlackKnight; Granny's licorice; Pixie Caramel; Chokito; Chocolate Raisins/<BR>Peanuts; Nut Roll; Crunch; Regina confectionery, including Marshmellows,Party Mix, Pineapple Chunks, Strawberry Hearts and Choc Orange Slices; Nutoatabars; Canterbury Oaty bars. <BR><b>Cooking products:</b> Nestl&eacute; baking cocoa, Nestl&eacute; cooking chocolate,Chocolate Melts, Choc Bits, Milk Melts, Highlander condensed milk, ReducedCream, Quick Custard Mix.<BR><b>Processed food:</b> Maggi; Findus frozen food, including Lean Cuisine; Buitonipasta and sauces; Nanda pasta; Crosse &amp; Blackwell relishes/pickles.<BR><b>Pet food:</b> Friskies, Go Cat, Cat Meow, Fancy Feast, Tux, Trusty.<BR><b>Dairy products: </b>Yoplait<BR><b>Supermarket own-name brands:</b> <i>According to our survey Nestl&eacute; onlymakes two such products for supermarket chains in Aotearoa:</i> No Frills Mueslibars and Pams Condensed Milk.<p><b>AUSTRALIA</b><BR>Baby Food Action Group, Community Aid Abroad, 156 George St, Fitzroy, Vic3065. Tel: (03) 419 7111.<BR><b>Beverages:</b> Nescaf&eacute;, including Gold Blend, Decaff; Milo; Caro; Slender.<BR><b>Dairy products:</b> Carnation, Coffeemate, Ideal, Tip-Top.<BR><b>Confectionery:</b> Kit Kat, Rowntree, Aero, After Eight, Smarties, Baci, BlackMagic, Fruit Pastilles, Milky Bar, Quality Street, Rolo.<BR><b>Mineral water:</b> Perrier, Vittel.<BR><b>Processed food: </b>Findus, Maggi, Lean Cuisine, Branston Pickle.<BR><b>Cereals:</b> Shredded Wheat.<BR><b>Pet food:</b> Go-Cat, Go-Dog.<BR><b>Cosmetics: </b>L'Oreal, Lancome.<BR><BR><img width=196 height=143 align=right hspace=5 vspace=5 src="boycott_kitkat.jpg"><br><b>BRITAIN</b><BR>Baby Milk Action, 23 St Andrews St, Cambridge CB2 3AX. Tel: (01223) 464420.Fax: (01223) 464417. E-mail: babymilkacti@gn.apc.org<BR><b>Beverages:</b> Nescaf&eacute;, including Gold Blend, Blend 37, Alta Rica, CapColombie, Cappuccino, Decaff, Fine Blend; Milo; Build-up; Caro; Elevenses;Flo-Mix; Libby's C Drinks; Mix-O-Choc, Moonshine; Nescor&eacute;; Nesfit;Nesquik; Slender; Superquik; Um Bongo.<BR><b>Confectionery:</b> Kit Kat, Rowntree, Aero, After Eight, Polo, Smarties, LionBar, Quality Street, Rolo, Toffee Crisp, Toffo, Walnut Whip, Weekend, Yorkie,Matchmakers, Milky Bar, Munchies, Black Magic, Fox's Glacier Mints, FruitPastilles, Animal bar, Baci, Blue Riband, Breakaway, Cabana, Caramac, CaramelWafer, Cello, Creamola, Dairy Crunch, Drifter, Eclipse, Good News, Festival,Gray&amp; Dunn biscuits, Jellytots, Karima, Montego, Novo, RPC, Savana,Secret, Tooty Frooties.<BR><b>Ice cream: </b>Lyons Maid.<BR><b>Cereals:</b> Shredded Wheat, Shreddies, Cheerios, Cinnamon Toast Crunch, CocoaPuffs, Crisp Rice, Energen, Force, Golden Grahams, Lucky Charms, Team, Robertson'scornflakes, Sunny Jim, Wheatflakes.<BR><b>Dairy products:</b> Carnation, Chambourcy, Coffeemate, Fussells, Ideal, Milkmaid,Tip-Top, Bonjour, Chamby, Creme Vienna, Darlky, Flanby, Fulcreem custard,Hippopota, Jacky, Kremly, Le Grande, Nouvelle, Robot.<BR><b>Mineral water:</b> Perrier, Ashbourne, Contrex&eacute;ville, Vittel, Vittelloise.<BR><b>Processed food:</b> Findus, Buitoni pasta &amp; canned foods, Crosse &amp; Blackwell,Maggi, Alphabetti, Bonne Cuisine, Dish of the Day, Eskimo, Four Seasons,Healthy Balance, Lean Cuisine, Pasta choice, Rice &amp; Things, Scrunchies,Waistline.<BR><b>Spreads/pickles:</b> Branston, Gales honey, Holgates honey, Pan-Yan, Sun-pat,Tartex, Vessen pat&eacute;.<BR><b>Seasonings:</b> British Shoyu, British vinegars, Cook-in-the-Pot, Dufrais, Sarsons.<BR><b>Cosmetics and eye care:</b> L'Oreal, Lancome, Claudel, Alcon.<BR><b>Pet foods: </b>Friskies, Go-Cat, Go-Dog.<BR><b>Supermarket own-name brands:</b><i> Most supermarket chains refuse to reveal thesources of their own-name products but both Tesco and the Co-op deservecredit for having come clean with us to allow consumers an informed choice.Nestl&eacute; makes Tesco's Corn Flakes, Sultana Bran, Bran Flakes, CocoaPuffs, Puffed Rice and Cocoa Flakes and the Co-op's Peanut Butter, RichChocolate Mousse and Easy Serve Ice Cream. Nestl&eacute; makes nothing forBudgen. But Sainsbury and Safeway refused to tell us and should not be rewardedfor this: all their own-brand cereals, dairy products and ice cream shouldbe treated with suspicion.</i><BR><BR><img width=142 height=153 align=right hspace=5 vspace=5 src="boycott_loreal.jpg"><br><b>CANADA/UNITED STATES</b><BR>IN-FACT Coalition, 10 Trinity Square, Toronto, Ont, M5G 1B1. Tel: (416)595 9819. Fax: (416) 591 9355. Web site: www.io.org/@infacto<BR><b>Beverages: </b>Nescaf&eacute;, Nestea, Chase &amp; Sandborn, Hills Brothers,Coffeemate, Movenpick, MJB, Taster's Choice, Encore, Club, Carnation, Libby'sjuices, Calistoga, Goodhost.<BR><b>Confectionery: </b>Laura Secord, Chunky Goobers, Coffee Crisp, Aero, Baci, QualityStreet, Nestl&eacute; Beich fundraising chocolate, Kit Kat, Smarties, AfterEight, Baby Ruth, Bit O Honey, Butterfinger, Alpine White Chocolate, Crunch,Raisinats, Black Magic, Turtles, Mirage.<BR>Ice cream: Laura Secord, Crunch, Drumstick, Mr Big, Haagen Dazs ice-creambars.<BR><b>Mineral Water:</b> Perrier, Vittel, Poland Spring.<BR>Processed food: Stouffers, Lean Cuisine, Buitoni, Contadina, Cresse &amp;Blackwell, Maggi, MJB.<BR><b>Cosmetics/eye care:</b> L'Oreal, Warner, Alcon.<BR>Wines: Beringer, Chateau Souverain, Los Hermanos, Nappa Ridge.<BR><i>Nestle has marketing agreements in North America with Nabisco, Walt Disney,Movenpick, Ault Foods (Sealtest Dairies) and Coca Cola (Nestea).</i><BR><BR><center><img width=400 height=135 hspace=5 vspace=5 src="boycott_products.jpg"></center><BR><BR><HR>&copy