<body>

<p><p>


<p>
<h2>TRAIN AS A VIDEO JOURNALIST</h2>
<br clear=left>

Spend one month in London, working as a video journalist for Channel One.  Salary £150 per week.  No air fares.  Age: under 30.<p>
 Must be a graduate, with journalistic experience in press, radio or tv, working for a Commonwealth broadcasting organisation, 
and excellent English - good enough to broadcast in, live.<p>

<b>How to apply:</b><br>
Write with a cv and a recommendation from an editor for whom the applicant has worked, giving dates when the applicant could be available, to:<br><b> Mrs Elizabeth Smith<br>
 CBA<br>
Broadcasting House<br>
 London W1A 1AA<br>
 Fax: +44 (0)171 765 5152</b><p>
  The CBA will shortlist and pass shortlisted candidates on to Channel One.  Channel One hope to take one trainee per month.

<p>


©Copyright:  CBA, September 1995
<p>

