<html><head><title>FEEDBACK</title><!!keys: ></head><body> <h2>Widows in Development Panel at NGO Beijing </h2>Margaret Owen, whose book <b>"Widows in Development: Seclusion and Exclusion"</b> will be published by ZED Books in 1996will be attending the NGO Forum in Beijing to discuss aspects of widowhood in developing countries.<p>She can be contacted there at the Dong Huan Estate in Huairou (reg no 7931) or in the UK on 44 (0) 17255 552327 (e-mail 100066.1321@compuserve.com) by anyone wishing to participate in an informal meeting to discuss policy issues concerning the status of widows.<p> Themes include: <ul><li>residence and inheritance rights; <li>marriage;<li>violence and legal protection;<li> support for widows and children; <li>economic activity; <li>human rights; <li>practices under custom and religious law. </ul><p>The meeting will be informal since the Population Council, initially involved in planning this activity, have decided not to come to Beijing. Anyone who has worked on the problems and constraints of widowhood is welcome to attend. Look out for the poster for time and place. <p><hr></body></html>
